        "cooked": "<p><a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/semisol\">@Semisol</a> maybe you can suggest. We have</p>\n<ul>\n<li>9 baremetal server (120CPU, 512Gb RAM, 2x3Tb NVME + 1 Raid SSD for system)</li>\n<li>FDB version 7.1.67</li>\n<li>on separated disk we run 7 tlog, 7 storage, 4 stateless</li>\n<li>redundancy mode three-data-hall</li>\n<li>current workload 10K TPS (we want increase it) on write (1R + 1W ops), value size about 4Kb</li>\n<li>52 Logs, 16 commit proxy, 4 GRV</li>\n<li>GRV and commit proxy has utilization 80+%</li>\n<li>each commit proxy has throughput about 250Mb/s</li>\n</ul>\n<p>How we can increase hardware utilization? Maybe scale storage or TLog?</p>",
