        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/semisol/{size}/1960_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-17T09:19:53.383Z",
        "cooked": "<p>You do not need a dedicated disk for stateless processes, or one at all. Allocate that disk to something more useful</p>\n<p>What\u2019s the full hardware specs? (individual disks, CPU cores and RAM in GB)</p>\n<p>You should have <em>only one TLog per disk</em>. For SS, you should have 3 max. for most NVMes</p>\n<p>This should improve performance</p>",
        "post_number": 9,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 10,
