        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/semisol/{size}/1960_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-17T09:55:27.582Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Your hosts are oversized. FDB at some point does not gain much from vertical scaling, but horizontal scaling.</p>\n<p>I have personally found the sweet-spot for bare metal to be 16 cores and 128GB of RAM, putting 3.84TB disks for SS and 512GB for TLog + un-RAIDed boot drive (can even be a USB!).</p>\n<p>Ask your infrastructure department if they can provide smaller hosts.</p>",
